From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

Spanish

[edit]

Alternative forms

[edit]
  • obscurecer

Etymology

[edit]

From oscuro (“dark”) +‎ -ecer.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /oskuɾeˈθeɾ/ [os.ku.ɾeˈθeɾ] (Spain)
  • IPA(key): /oskuɾeˈseɾ/ [os.ku.ɾeˈseɾ] (Latin America, Philippines)
  • Audio (Colombia):(file)
  • Rhymes: -eɾ
  • Syllabification: os‧cu‧re‧cer

Verb

[edit]

oscurecer (first-person singular present oscurezco, first-person singular preterite oscurecí, past participle oscurecido)

  1. to darken
